cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses scheduling MapReduce jobs on cloud-based data processing environments, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel scheduler to address the problem of scheduling MR jobs to meet deadlines while maximizing data locality and resource utilization. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses a software solution for scheduling data-intensive workloads on MapReduce based clouds. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a dynamic resource reconfiguration approach for scheduling MR jobs to meet completion time goals. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the MapReduce programming model and proposes a scheduler for running data-intensive applications on the cloud.
